<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="230" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1216,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName box="[314,620,1216,1242]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="amylosporum">
<emphasis box="[314,620,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Astrothelium amylosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 4 ascospores per ascus, in the smaller ascospores, and in the ascomata being mostly covered by a thallus layer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
